1. Web Scraping -
Hotel data was collected from an online booking website using Selenium and BeautifulSoup.
The scraper extracts information such as:

Hotel Name
Price
Rating
Location
City

Data was collected for multiple cities including Pune, Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Ahmedabad, and Kolkata.

2. Data Cleaning -
After collecting the data, several preprocessing steps were performed:

Removed duplicate records
Handled missing values
Standardized column names
Converted data types where required
Added a city column to identify the location

3. Data Integration -
All city datasets were combined into a single dataset using the Pandas library to simplify analysis.

4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) -

EDA was conducted to understand trends and patterns in the dataset.
Some of the analysis performed includes:
Distribution of hotel prices
City-wise hotel comparisons
Rating distribution
Relationship between price and ratings
Visualizations were created using Matplotlib and Seaborn.

